cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with change detection in remotely sensed images, which is a common problem in computer vision. The proposed approach involves image fusion, which is a common technique in computer vision and image processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves prediction and decision-making, which are related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) likely sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper deals with multispectral and hyperspectral images, which are related to multimedia processing, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible sub-category.
